  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add onion, carrot, celery and garlic; saut\u00e9 5\u202fmin until softened.",
    "Stir in white wine, let reduce for 2\u202fmin to deglaze the pan, scraping up brown bits.",
    "Add snow peas and vegetable broth; bring to a gentle boil.",
    "Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10\u202fmin until peas are tender.",
    "Season with salt, pepper, and dried dill; adjust as needed.",
    "Use an immersion blender to partially puree for a silky texture, or leave chunky for contrast.",
    "Serve warm, or allow to cool and store in airtight containers for up to 3 days."
  ],
